==English==

===Etymology 1===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*per-|id=before}}
From {{inh|en|enm|for-}}, {{m|enm|vor-}}, {{m|enm|ver-}}, from {{inh|en|ang|for-}}, {{m|ang|fer-}}, {{m|ang|f√¶r-}}, {{m|ang|fyr-|pos=prefix|t=far, away, completely}}, from the merger of {{inh|en|gem-pro|*fra-}} {{gloss|"away, away from"; see {{l|en|fro}}, {{l|en|from}}}} and {{inh|en|gem-pro|*fur-}}, {{m|gem-pro|*far-|t=through, completely, fully}}, from {{inh|en|ine-pro|*pro-}}, {{m|ine-pro|*per-}}, {{m|ine-pro|*pr-}}. Cognate with {{cog|sco|for-}}, {{cog|fy|fer-}}, {{m|fy|for-}}, {{cog|nl|ver-}}, {{cog|de|ver-}}, {{cog|sv|f√∂r-}}, {{cog|da|for-}}, {{cog|no|for-}}, {{cog|got|êçÜêçÇêå∞-}}, {{cog|la|pro-}}. More at {{l|en|for}}.

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|en|/f…îÀê(…π)/|a=stressed}}
* {{IPA|en|/f…ô(…π)/|a=unstressed}}

====Prefix====
{{en-prefix}}

# {{senseid|en|forth}} {{lb|en|no longer productive}} [[forth|Forth]]: prefixed to verbs to indicate a direction of 'away', 'off', 'forth'.
#: {{uxi|en|[[forsteal|'''for'''steal]]}} is to steal away, {{uxi|en|[[forloppin|'''for'''loppin]]}} is being a runaway, {{uxi|en|[[forban|'''for'''ban]]}} is to exile, {{uxi|en|[[fordrive|'''for'''drive]]}} is to drive away, {{uxi|en|[[fortake|'''for'''take]]}} is to take away, {{uxi|en|[[forthrow|'''for'''throw]]}} is to throw off, {{uxi|en|[[forshake|'''for'''shake]]}} is to shake off, {{uxi|en|[[forhow|'''for'''how]]}} is to cast off
# {{senseid|en|exhausting}} {{lb|en|no longer productive}} [[exhausting|Exhausting]]: prefixed to verbs with the sense of wearing or exhausting one's self.
#: {{uxi|en|[[forsing|'''for'''sing]]}} is to sing to exhaustion, {{uxi|en|[[forwander|'''for'''wander]]}} is to wander until weary, {{uxi|en|[[fortravel|'''for'''travel]]}} is to tire by travelling
# {{senseid|en|destructively}} {{lb|en|no longer productive}} [[destructively|Destructively]]: prefixed to verbs with the sense of destruction or pain.
#: {{uxi|en|[[forhang|'''for'''hang]]}} is to hang to death, {{uxi|en|[[forthink|'''for'''think]]}} is to cause distress or regret to, {{uxi|en|[[fordo|'''for'''do]]}} is to kill
# {{senseid|en|wrongly}} {{lb|en|no longer productive}} [[wrongly|Wrongly]]: prefixed to verbs with the sense of wrongly, amorally.
#: {{uxi|en|[[forteach|'''for'''teach]]}} is to misteach, {{uxi|en|[[forswear|'''for'''swear]]}} is to commit perjury, {{uxi|en|[[forworship|'''for'''worship]]}} is to worship wrongly, {{uxi|en|[[forlead|'''for'''lead]]}} is to mislead, {{uxi|en|[[forlive|'''for'''live]]}} is to live pervertedly
# {{senseid|en|neglectfully}} {{lb|en|no longer productive}} [[neglectfully|Neglectfully]]: prefixed to verbs with the sense of abstaining from or neglecting.
#: {{uxi|en|[[forslip|'''for'''slip]]}} is to allow someone or something to escape by letting them slip by; {{uxi|en|[[forslug|'''for'''slug]]}} is to lose, neglect, or destroy by sluggishness; {{uxi|en|[[forslack|'''for'''slack]]}} is to lose or spoil by slackness
# {{senseid|en|very}} {{lb|en|no longer productive}} [[very|Very]]: intensifying adjectives.
#: {{uxi|en|[[forblack|'''for'''black]]}} is extremely black, {{uxi|en|[[forswollen|'''for'''swollen]]}} is excessively swollen
# {{senseid|en|making}} {{lb|en|no longer productive}} [[making|Making]]: prefixed to verbs to indicate the subject takes the character of the verb.
#: {{uxi|en|[[fordote|'''for'''dote]]}} is to make foolish or doting, {{uxi|en|[[forguilt|'''for'''guilt]]}} is to bring into a state of guilt
# {{senseid|en|excessively}} {{lb|en|no longer productive}} [[excessively|Excessively]]: prefixed to verbs with the sense of doing so in excessive or overwhelm.
#: {{uxi|en|[[forwax|'''for'''wax]]}} is to grow to excess, {{uxi|en|[[forgrow|'''for'''grow]]}} is to grow to excess, {{uxi|en|[[forhare|'''for'''hare]]}} is to affright or harry exceedingly
# {{senseid|en|excluding}} {{lb|en|no longer productive}} [[excluding|Excluding]]: prefixed to verbs to give the sense of prohibition or exclusion.
#: {{uxi|en|[[forjudge|'''for'''judge]]}} is to exclude by a judgment, {{uxi|en|[[forshut|'''for'''shut]]}} is to shut off or out, {{uxi|en|[[forbar|'''for'''bar]]}} is to exclude
# {{senseid|en|intensively}} {{lb|en|no longer productive}} [[intensively|Intensively]]
#: {{uxi|en|[[forbeat|'''for'''beat]]}} is to beat, {{uxi|en|[[fordread|'''for'''dread]]}} is to be in dread of, {{uxi|en|[[forlay|'''for'''lay]]}} is to lie in wait for
# {{senseid|en|thoroughly}} {{lb|en|no longer productive}} [[thoroughly|Thoroughly]]: prefixed to verbs with the sense of thoroughly, all over.
#: {{uxi|en|[[forgrow|'''for'''grow]]}} is to become grown over or become covered with growth, {{uxi|en|[[forbathe|'''for'''bathe]]}} is to bathe abundantly or thoroughly, {{uxi|en|[[forseek|'''for'''seek]]}} is to seek thoroughly, {{uxi|en|[[forwrap|'''for'''wrap]]}} is to wrap up

