==Middle English==

===Alternative forms===
* {{alter|enm|far-|fer-|vor-|ver-}}

===Etymology===
From {{inh|enm|ang|for-}}, from {{inh|enm|gmw-pro|*fra-}}, from {{inh|enm|gem-pro|*fra-}}, from {{inh|enm|ine-pro|*pro-}}.

The Old English prefix was reinforced by {{inh|enm|gmw-pro|*furi-}}, from {{inh|enm|gem-pro|*furi-}}; In Middle English, this prefix is further reinforced by {{der|enm|fro|for-}}, from {{der|enm|la|foris}}.

